<subSubSection pageId="12" pageNumber="101" type="notes">
<paragraph pageId="12" pageNumber="101">Notes.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="12" pageNumber="101">
<taxonomicName class="Sordariomycetes" family="Melanconidaceae" genus="Melanconis" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Melanconis stilbostoma" order="Diaporthales" pageId="12" pageNumber="101" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="stilbostoma">Melanconis stilbostoma</taxonomicName>
is the type species of 
<taxonomicName class="Sordariomycetes" family="Melanconidaceae" genus="Melanconis" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Melanconis" order="Diaporthales" pageId="12" pageNumber="101" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="genus">Melanconis</taxonomicName>
and is thus far only known to occur on 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Betulaceae" genus="Betula" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Betula" order="Fagales" pageId="12" pageNumber="101" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">Betula</taxonomicName>
spp. with a worldwide distribution (
<bibRefCitation author="Fan, XL" journalOrPublisher="Persoonia" pageId="21" pageNumber="110" url="http://doi.org/10.1007/s11557-016-1163-2" year="2016">Fan et al. 2016</bibRefCitation>
). 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Betulaceae" genus="Betula" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Betula pendula" order="Fagales" pageId="12" pageNumber="101" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="pendula">Betula pendula</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName genus="B." lsidName="B. rotundifolia" pageId="12" pageNumber="101" rank="species" species="rotundifolia">B. rotundifolia</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName genus="B." lsidName="B. tianschanica" pageId="12" pageNumber="101" rank="species" species="tianschanica">B. tianschanica</taxonomicName>
are recorded as hosts in China (
<bibRefCitation pageId="12" pageNumber="101">Zhuang 2005</bibRefCitation>
). The current investigation suggested that this species is restricted to and widespread on 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Betulaceae" genus="Betula" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Betula platyphylla" order="Fagales" pageId="12" pageNumber="101" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="platyphylla">Betula platyphylla</taxonomicName>
in China.
</paragraph>
